Rationale for In-Role Promotion – Hamish [Last Name]

Hamish has been with the bank for over seven years and has consistently expanded his responsibilities. Over the past two years, his role has grown significantly from a supportive AVP capacity into one that fully reflects a VP position.

Leadership & Impact: Hamish now leads the screening portfolio independently, delivering models that are both robust and high-performing. This work has resulted in savings of over 100 FTEs and established a strong foundation of reliability in a critical area.

Technical Expertise: Leveraging his previous experience at Barclays and his extensive network, Hamish is the go-to person for development platform support. He has gone above and beyond to ensure colleagues have access to the most efficient environment possible, despite structural limitations.

Stakeholder Engagement: Hamish has developed strong relationships across the bank and is regarded as a trusted ML expert driving innovation. He has received numerous recognitions from both colleagues and senior stakeholders.

Innovation & Efficiency: Most recently, Hamish has been driving the automation of our data curation capabilities, enhancing efficiency and reliability across the team.


Given the scope of his leadership, his technical authority, and his sustained delivery of measurable impact, Hamish’s current contribution is firmly at the VP level. His promotion would recognize both his achievements and the responsibilities he already carries.


