Rationale for In-Role Promotion – Hao [Last Name]

Hao joined Barclays three years ago at AVP level, bringing with him extensive experience in credit risk modelling and software engineering, including a PhD in High Energy Physics. From the outset, he was recruited with the expectation of rapid progression, and over this period he has evolved from an individual contributor into a leader delivering VP-level impact.

Leadership & Delivery: Hao has taken end-to-end ownership of high-impact projects, including the delivery of the first-generation USCB Transaction Monitoring ML model and its integration with SAM8. This initiative significantly improved alert quality and reduced operational workload, saving approximately 15 FTEs.

Innovation & Efficiency: He independently optimized the SAM8 rule simulation process, reducing the cycle from months to days. This work improved alert performance and lowered technology costs by eliminating reliance on high-cost UAT environments.

Technical Authority: Hao is currently leading development of the next-generation IFC Transaction Monitoring ML model, which will become the primary engine for alert generation—further enhancing detection and system resilience.

Collaboration & Influence: He proactively engages stakeholders across FIU operations, TMCS, and business teams to drive model improvements. He is widely recognized for clear communication, rapid delivery, and trusted expertise.

Coaching & Growth: Beyond delivery, Hao provides critical support in onboarding and mentoring junior hires, offering technical guidance and strengthening the team’s long-term capability.


Hao’s consistent delivery, technical depth, and stakeholder engagement have expanded his remit well beyond the scope of an AVP. His current contribution and leadership are firmly at VP level, and his promotion would rightly recognize the impact he is already making.


